race.comment: WHY WHY WHY (12) resumes and has the numbers to be winning. He was beaten 1.5L at Goulburn three starts back on debut and raced in stronger provincial company over a mile following. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and his recent Kembla Grange trial suggests he's ready to go. SHUTTERING (8) resumes for Luke Pepper and has switched from a top Sydney barn on a 156-day return. She showed enough two-back on debut to suggest this is achievable and she finally draws an inside gate. The in-form Boudvillain is booked and that's a decent push for her chances. FLYING GABBI (1) debuts from the inside barrier and went close in a recent Canberra trial. Has to be considered. Ditto stablemate LIAMENA AVENUE (7), who resumed with a place at the Sapphire Coast and is further improved. The gate is a touch awkward, but she has weight relief and further upside.
